Redd Locations and Habitat Utilization

Maddee Wiggins (FlowWest)

2026-01-05

Objective

Using mini snorkel data from the Feather River, make a visual to understand if habitat utilization and location of redds is correlated.

Remove zero Redds

Remove locations that have zero redd

Redd data over time

This visual represents the number of redds over time at each location. It helps provide context on which sites generally have redds and if they have redds consistently over time.

Map of habitat and redds

This map provides context into the habitat transect locations, identified by whether they are in the high flow HFC or low flow LFC part of the Feather River. Redds cluster around habitat transect locations but in no consistent manner and are only shown as far south as McFarland Riffle.
